A vintage 1950s advertisement style illustration showing four cheerful cartoon programmers sitting at retro computer terminals in a row, three of them with modern sleek screens displaying curly braces and modern code symbols, while the fourth programmer sits proudly at an old-fashioned beige terminal with a green monochrome screen, looking slightly defiant but content. The scene has warm sepia tones with pops of mustard yellow and teal, halftone dot patterns in the background, and a nostalgic mid-century aesthetic with rounded furniture and atomic-age decorative elements. The fourth programmer wears a cardigan while the others sport trendy modern attire, capturing a playful tension between legacy and contemporary technology.
